---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Whole-Home Remodeling | Complete Transformations in Venezuela"
  description="Full-service whole-home remodeling with architectural vision, permit handling, and project management. Transform your entire property in Valencia, San Diego and Caracas."
  image="/images/integrales-800.webp"
  activePage="services"
>
  <header class="article-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image: url('/images/integrales-800.webp')"></div>
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <a href="/en/services" class="back-link">← Back to Services</a>
      <span class="article-category">Premium Service</span>
      <h1 class="article-title"><span class="line">Whole-Home</span><span class="line gold">Remodeling</span></h1>
      <p class="article-excerpt">Complete transformation of your home or business with professional management and full warranty.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="article-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>A whole-home remodel is far more than renovating a space. It's completely reimagining your home or business, optimizing every square foot, updating systems, and creating an environment that reflects your current lifestyle. It's a significant investment that, when executed correctly, transforms your quality of life and significantly increases your property value.</p>

        <p>At ReformaT Venezuela, we combine over 20 years of industry experience with our presence in Venezuela for nearly 2 years, bringing advanced techniques and European standards adapted to the local market of Valencia and San Diego.</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-proyecto-completo.webp" alt="Fully completed whole-home remodel showcasing multiple transformed spaces" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <h2>What's Included in a Whole-Home Remodel?</h2>

        <p>A whole-home remodel covers absolutely everything needed to transform a space from start to finish. We don't leave anything half-done. We handle every detail so you only have to worry about choosing finishes and enjoying the result.</p>

        <h3>Demolition and Preparation Phase</h3>

        <p><strong>Complete removal:</strong> We eliminate elements that won't be kept with responsible debris management. We remove partitions, old flooring, tiles, fixtures, outdated systems, and any element that interferes with the new design.</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-demolicion.webp" alt="Controlled demolition process with professional debris removal during whole-home remodel" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <p><strong>Element protection:</strong> We professionally cover doors, windows, and architectural elements to be preserved. We protect building common areas and elevators during construction.</p>

        <p><strong>Structural preparation:</strong> We reinforce structures, level floors, and prepare surfaces for new finishes. Crack repair, slab consolidation, and moisture treatment when necessary.</p>

        <h3>Complete Technical Installations</h3>

        <p><strong>Electrical:</strong> Complete renovation with modern protection, proper wiring, and certified grounding. New electrical panel with GFCI breakers and circuit breakers, independent circuits for kitchen, bathrooms, and high-demand areas.</p>

        <p><strong>Plumbing:</strong> Replacement of old pipes with durable materials, complete system, and pressure testing. Copper, PEX, or multilayer pipes depending on application, with independent shut-off valves per zone.</p>

        <p><strong>HVAC:</strong> Installation of air conditioning systems, mechanical ventilation, and thermal insulation. Ductwork, split systems, or centralized systems based on space needs.</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-instalaciones.webp" alt="Visible plumbing and electrical rough-in installations during whole-home remodel" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <h2>Comprehensive Project Management</h2>

        <p>A whole-home remodel involves coordinating dozens of specialized trades: demolition, framing, plumbing, electrical, HVAC, carpentry, painting, flooring, and finishing. We serve as your single point of contact, managing all subcontractors, schedules, and quality control.</p>

        <p>Our dedicated project manager visits your property daily, provides weekly progress reports with photos and videos, and ensures every detail meets our quality standards before moving to the next phase.</p>

        <h2>Architectural Vision & Space Planning</h2>

        <p>We don't just renovate rooms; we reimagine how you live in your space. Our design process includes:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Space Analysis:</strong> Evaluating current flow, natural light, and structural possibilities</li>
          <li><strong>Layout Optimization:</strong> Removing walls, adding openings, reconfiguring rooms for modern living</li>
          <li><strong>3D Visualization:</strong> Photorealistic renders so you see exactly what you'll get before construction begins</li>
          <li><strong>Material Selection:</strong> Guided selection of finishes, fixtures, and surfaces that match your style and budget</li>
        </ul>

        <img src="/images/integrales-plano-diseno.webp" alt="Architectural floor plan and 3D render design for whole-home remodel showing space layout" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <h2>Permit Handling & Regulatory Compliance</h2>

        <p>Navigating Venezuelan building regulations can be complex. We handle all permit applications, structural engineering approvals, and inspections required for your project. This protects you from legal issues and ensures your renovation adds value to your property.</p>

        <h2>Before & After: Real Transformations</h2>

        <p>The best way to understand the impact of a whole-home remodel is to see it with your own eyes. Here's a real transformation example:</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-antes.webp" alt="Before state of whole-home remodel showing outdated and dysfunctional space" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <p>The initial state showed compartmentalized spaces, outdated systems, lack of natural light, and inefficient layout. Every corner had functional and aesthetic problems.</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-despues.webp" alt="After state of whole-home remodel with open, bright, and completely renovated spaces" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <p>The result is a completely transformed space: open layout that maximizes natural light, completely renovated systems, premium finishes, and functionality optimized for the client's current lifestyle.</p>

        <h2>Types of Whole-Home Projects We Handle</h2>

        <p><strong>Aging Property Modernization:</strong> Updating electrical systems, plumbing, windows, and insulation to modern standards while preserving architectural character.</p>

        <p><strong>Open-Concept Conversions:</strong> Removing walls to create flowing living spaces that connect kitchen, dining, and living areas.</p>

        <p><strong>Multi-Story Additions:</strong> Adding square footage through vertical or horizontal expansion with proper structural engineering.</p>

        <p><strong>Investor Property Preparation:</strong> Turnkey renovations optimized for rental ROI or resale value, with documentation for U.S. tax purposes.</p>

        <h2>The Whole-Home Process: From Idea to Reality</h2>

        <h3>Phase 1: Discovery (2-3 weeks)</h3>
        <p>Initial consultation, site measurements, systems evaluation, needs assessment, and conceptual design development.</p>

        <h3>Phase 2: Design & Planning (3-4 weeks)</h3>
        <p>We prepare a detailed line-item quote. Technical plans, 3D renders, material selection, permit applications, and final budget approval. We sign a contract with dates and warranty.</p>

        <h3>Phase 3: Pre-Construction (2 weeks)</h3>
        <p>Material ordering, subcontractor scheduling, site preparation, and protection of existing spaces. We coordinate with suppliers to ensure materials are ready at construction start.</p>

        <h3>Phase 4: Construction (1-3 months)</h3>
        <p><strong>The 1-3 month timeline begins here, from the start of construction work.</strong></p>

        <p><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Demolition, surface preparation, technical installations (plumbing, electrical, HVAC).</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-albanileria.webp" alt="Framing and masonry work in progress during whole-home remodel" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <p><strong>Week 3-5:</strong> Framing, drywall, waterproofing, and surface finishes. Wall construction, flooring installation, and tile work.</p>

        <p><strong>Week 6-10:</strong> Carpentry, fixtures, painting, lighting, and final finishes. Cabinet installation, door fitting, and trim work.</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-acabados.webp" alt="Final finish details with painting, lighting, and trim work in whole-home remodel" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <h3>Phase 5: Final Walkthrough & Warranty</h3>
        <p>Comprehensive inspection, punch list completion, warranty delivery, and complete documentation. Professional cleaning included.</p>

        <h2>Our Professional Team</h2>

        <p>We have an in-house team of professionals specialized in each trade. We don't subcontract critical project components, which allows us to maintain total control over quality and timelines.</p>

        <img src="/images/integrales-equipo-trabajando.webp" alt="Professional team working in coordinated manner on whole-home remodel construction site" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <p>Licensed plumbers, certified electricians, experienced masons, precision carpenters, finish painters, and tile specialists work under direct supervision of our project manager.</p>

        <h2>Budget Transparency</h2>

        <p>Whole-home remodels require detailed budgeting. We provide line-item quotes that break down every cost: demolition, structural work, installations, finishes, fixtures, appliances, and labor. No hidden fees, no surprises.</p>

        <p><strong>Basic Remodel:</strong> Custom quote. Includes: demolition, basic installations, standard finishes, functional fixtures.</p>

        <p><strong>Mid-Range Remodel:</strong> Custom quote. Includes: premium installations, quality finishes, recognized brand fixtures, complete LED lighting.</p>

        <p><strong>Premium Remodel:</strong> Custom quote. Includes: exclusive materials, smart home integration, luxury finishes, complete custom design.</p>

        <p><em>Note: All quotes are personalized. Schedule a free consultation to receive a detailed estimate based on your specific needs.</em></p>

        <h2>Why Choose ReformaT Venezuela?</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Single point of contact</strong> for entire project</li>
          <li><strong>20+ years managing</strong> complex renovations</li>
          <li><strong>Full permit handling</strong> and regulatory compliance</li>
          <li><strong>Weekly reports</strong> with photos and videos</li>
          <li><strong>In-house team:</strong> We don't subcontract, we supervise every detail</li>
          <li><strong>Structural engineering partnerships</strong> when needed</li>
          <li><strong>Fixed-price contracts</strong> with detailed scope</li>
          <li><strong>Local knowledge:</strong> We understand the particularities of Valencia and San Diego</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Next Step</h2>

        <p>If you're considering a whole-home remodel, the first step is a free consultation. No commitment. We simply listen to your needs, evaluate the space, and explain the possibilities.</p>

        <p>During the visit:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>We evaluate current system conditions</li>
          <li>We identify improvement opportunities</li>
          <li>We take precise measurements</li>
          <li>We listen to your vision and needs</li>
          <li>We show you examples of similar projects</li>
          <li>We answer all your questions</li>
          <li>We give you an indicative budget range</li>
        </ul>

        <p>If you decide to move forward, within a few days you'll have a complete design with 3D renders and detailed quote. If not, at least you'll have a professional evaluation of your space.</p>

        <p><strong>Ready to transform your space?</strong> <a href="/en/contact">Schedule your free consultation</a> today.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-wrapper">
      <h2 class="cta-title">Ready for Your Complete Transformation?</h2>
      <p class="cta-text">Schedule a free consultation and receive a detailed whole-home remodeling proposal.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-premium btn-primary-premium">
        <span class="btn-content">Request a Quote</span>
        <span class="btn-border"></span>
        <span class="btn-shine"></span>
        <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-hero { position: relative; min-height: 80vh; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; justify-content: center; text-align: center; color: var(--white); overflow: hidden; padding-top: 140px; padding-bottom: 80px; }
  .hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background-size: cover; background-position: center; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.95) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.2) 100%); z-index: 2; }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 3; max-width: 900px; padding: 0 20px; }
  .article-category { display: inline-block; background: rgba(201,169,97,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--gold); color: var(--gold); padding: 8px 20px; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 25px; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .article-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .article-title .line { display: block; }
  .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.3rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 400; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: var(--gold); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 20px; transition: 0.3s; text-decoration: none; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold-light); }
  .article-section { padding: 80px 0; background: var(--white); }
  .article-body { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .article-body h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold); }
  .article-body ul, .article-body ol { margin: 1.5rem 0 1.5rem 2rem; }
  .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body img { 
    border-radius: 12px; 
    margin: 2.5rem 0; 
    box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); 
    width: 100%; 
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 3/2;
    object-fit: cover;
  }
  .article-body > p:first-of-type::first-letter { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 4.5rem; font-weight: 600; float: left; line-height: 0.75; margin-right: 0.15em; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 8px; }
  .cta-section { background: var(--bg); color: var(--white); text-align: center; padding: 110px 24px; width: 100%; }
  .cta-wrapper { max-width: 950px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  .cta-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--white); text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 45px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; font-weight: 400; text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-section .btn-premium { padding: 20px 55px; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article-hero { min-height: 70vh; padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 60px; }
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 3.5rem); }
    .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body h2 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .article-body img { margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .cta-section { padding: 90px 20px; }
    .cta-title { font-size: 2.2rem; }
    .cta-text { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>